--------------------------------------<br>
soloing spectres <br>
<br>
I've heard a lot about enchanters charm soloing the specs in oasis, and quite frankly that sounds like just about as much fun you can have without a gallon of shaving cream and a room full of monkeys!<br>
So, I wanted to ask a few questions about it. First and foremost, what's a good level to start trying these bad boys? I'm 31 now and I know that's still quite early. But I've seen a post saying as early as 34 they can be soloed up to 5 at a time.<br>
<br>
Secondly, what kind of tactics have people found useful? I mean, charm soloing of course, but any specific strategies or subtle nuances that will make my life easier?<br>
<br>
Third, anything else that anybody can think of that might help me out.<br>
<br>
My most significant charming experience to date has been with the aviaks in SK which brought me to 31. And, no need to post 'Always have sow on' ... I've figured that part out.    <br>
<br>
Thanks for any info ...<br>
-Yizzelar<br>
****************************************<br>
<br>
It's been a while, but let me see if I can give you some general info on soloing spectres.<br>
<br>
I think I started on them when the AC in UGuk quit giving me exp.  At 34, it will probably be touch and go, but do-able. You will certainly live, if you decide to run early enough. <br>
<br>
I've found the most difficult thing to do was to pull a fight I could handle. Usually the whole island of five is up there. <br>
<br>
Have SoW, and cast Illusion: Air Elemental, and have Rune III up. Best you can do is charm one, which will pull 3-5. Your charmed spec will taunt, and get agro off you, and at that point, you'd better start rooting them as fast as you can.<br>
<br>
The other specs will tear through your pet, but they'll be rooted at least when he dies.<br>
<br>
Charm another, repeat.  Do that until you have two left. Med while the specs thin down their numbers, and you should be fine. Then charm one, and drop a dot and a slow on the other. Sit down, and med up. That should give your pet the edge he needs to come out of the fight the winner, but bloody as hell. A root/nuke should finish off your pet when charm breaks.<br>
<br>
It's actually pretty easy to solo any number of specs, as long as you can manage agro, and keep the spectres rooted.<br>
<br>
Make sure to have all your self buffs up, (cha, ac, hp, mr, etc.).<br>
Modak<br>
50 Enchanter<br>
Quellious <br>
**********************************<br>
Hmm... well... Modak's advice was nice... but i do it differently... little more risk... but the payoff is great...<br>
-----<br>
Spells:<br>
current DD<br>
previous DD<br>
Tash<br>
Root<br>
Mez<br>
Charm<br>
Invis(unless your a DE, in wich case, you got charm kiting in the bag)<br>
Switch slot- self buffs for resting, Stun, in the event sow fades...<br>
--I personaly would take the time to camp AC and get jboots... makes me feel 100% more safe...<br>
<br>
ok.. sence you 31... id at least get 34 before trying this, but...<br>
Tash a spec and run(float) to gypsies - when the specs get TO the shore, use your best mez to mez one of them... keep this up till there are onlt 2 left.<br>
when you are down to 2 specs, charm one and root the other... when the specs are where they would normaly start to run... INVIS or HIDE... this will break charm, and if one spec is rooted, root the other... kill both and thats 2x the EXP... then procede to the rest of the specs that are mezzed...<br>
atr 44, i was able to take out the entire isle with 200int and my mana items... unless charm broke more then once.<br>
the main thing is... make sure you have some form of SoW or Jboots - otherwise, get a group... specs are NOT for you.<br>
- Spag<br>
- 48 Enchanter<br>
- Ambient Light<br>
- Zebuxoruk server <br>
**************************<br>
Here how i did it :<br>
First, please don't pull to gypsies, you will kill a lot of low level players, always pull to the inns ner the South Ro zone.<br>
With sow, air elemental form and rune III on, i pulled one with tashan. Then you run to the shore, and charm the one who is tashed asap.<br>
Normally, others spectres will agro him. Land an aoe mezz on your pet, ending with only 2 specs awake( your pet and another he fights).<br>
Fell free to assist your pet, break charm to finish it and charm another pet.<br>
As this i soloed the 5 specs, i didn't do it often cause the lag almost killed me each time <br>
Chaminou, gentlegnome en robe jaune. <br>
